text: Endometrial cancer is cancer in the endometrium (lining of the uterus). The cancer is usually diagnosed during its early stages, resulting in a better survival rate than most cancers. Endometrial cancer is the most common gynecologic cancer in the United States: over 35,000 women are diagnosed each year. Category:Medicine Category:Cancer C Category:Obstetrics and gynecology C
title: Endometrial cancer
